    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - HARD START AND NO START DIAGNOSTICS - Test Procedures - Glow Plug
        System (Components)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Glow Plug System (Components)</title>
        <figure id="f2400558" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD31/D3170.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, read all
                    safety instructions in the foreword of this manual. Follow all warnings, cautions, and notes.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Procedure</emph>
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Select the feed wiring loom for the glow plug side that failed.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove wires from the loom convolute.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install Current Clamp around one of the four wires and do the Glow Plug Output StateTest.
            </para>
            <para>After 40 seconds, measure amperage. Move Current Clamp to remaining wires one at a time. measuring
                amperage each time.
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>If not done within 120 seconds of starting Glow Plug Output State Test, repeat Glow Plug
                        Output State for the remaining glow plugs.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Record amperage on Hard Start and No Start Diagnostics form.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>If any glow plug failed, use a DMM to do steps 5 through 8.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2400559" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD31/D31132.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Resistance check between glow plug relay and glow plug</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check resistance of wire between the glow plug relay and glow plug.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Record resistance for each wire on diagnostics form.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2400560" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD31/D31117.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Glow plug resistance</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using glow plug test lead, check glow plug resistance to ground.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Record resistance for each suspect glow plug on dignostics form.</para>
        </step1>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Defective wiring harness connection</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Poor ground connection</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Defective glow plug relay</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Defective glow plugs</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Defective ECM</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
    </svcproc>
